issues.title: WildFly 10.0.0 / Cassandra 3.4 Pull Request
issues.body:
Hello,

I have a minor pull request that adjusts the source code to work with WildFly 10.0.0 and version 3.4 of the Cassandra driver. Are you willing to consider this pull request?

Cheers,
Michael

issues.title: Backwards compatibility with JBoss 7.1.2
issues.body:
DO NOT MERGE (into master).

This PR is intended to be a branch off of master that enables backwards compatibility with JBoss 7.1.2.  If you choose to accept, please create a similarly named branch, and merge my branch into that one.

Thanks,
Aaron

commit.message:
Merge pull request #6 from jmesnil/patch-1

Fix installation instructions

Merge pull request #5 from metlos/enable-2.1.5

Since we are using wildfly-cassandra primarily for development, I am not overly concerned right now about the System.exit() calls. Going forward though, I think we should release a version of wildfly-cassandra that uses C* 2.1.5 and then update master to require Cassandra trunk as it previously did.

Produce both module zip and an wildfly overlay zip.

Also fix the module.xml for C* 2.1.5.
Trivial - update the SCM in pom and remove commented out sections.

Adding support for running Cassandra 2.1.5.

Warning is issued that that might result in the server being shut down
abruptly.

This probably doesn't work properly, but that will be solved in the
future commits.
Reformatting to follow the Hawkular rules.

Merge pull request #4 from heiko-braun/master

merge PR from @ehsavoie

updating WildFly to 8.2.0 Final
Fixing nodetool after changes in cassandra-trunk

Merge pull request #3 from heiko-braun/master

Update to cassandra trunk (3.0.0-SNAPSHOT)

Merge pull request #2 from heiko-braun/master

Updated readme

Rename files and packages according to the Wildfly naming policy

See https://community.jboss.org/wiki/WildFlyNamingPolicy
Allow the data,commitlog & caches directories to be replaced (defaults to 'jboss.server.data.dir/xyz')
UPdate the readme to include a domain mode example
Inlcude cluster_name in storage directory. Fix broadcast addresses for SimpleSeedProvider
Use a domain wide system property to configreu the seed list
Some thoughts about the prerequisites added
Introduce custom cassandra daemon that works with the patched 2.0.6 library
Update the cassandra profile to relfect the new config
Fix test coverage: if attribute values equal the default value, then they are suppressed when persisting the XML
Refactor class names, chose more abbreviate terms
Rely on a single parser instance
Checkpoint: First working test coverage on new DMR parsers
WIP: move to simplified xml parsers
Switch back to SimpleSnitch for now
Remove embedded server helper. Introduce ConfigurationLoader (still delegtes to yaml file)
Move cassandra config to module directory (for now)
Additonal dependencies added: Deamon startup works
Packaging and starting daemon (fails due to access of sun.misc.Unsafe)
Hardcoded module references for now (needs to be fixed)
revert to system out logging until the loggers actually work
